<!-- 1.7.14 -->
<div class='toload proposition'>
	<p><span class='envidentifier'>Proposition 1.7.14</span>
	Suppose $\mu$ is a mean on a weakly Boolean semigroup $S$. Then</p>
	<ol class='alphpar'>
		<li> $\mu(0)=0$.
		<li> $\mu(e\lor f)=\mu(e)+\mu(f)-\mu(ef)$ for all $e,f\in E(S)$.
		<li> If $e\leq f$ in $E(S)$ then $\mu(f)=\mu(e)+\mu(f\setminus e)$.
	</ol>
</div>